1
Jerusalem being considered Judea and the land north of Jerusalem
1
2
being considered Samaria;
2
3
2. “Official government material” means a guidance, rule,
3
4
material, briefing, press release, or communication prepared by a
4
5
state agency; and
5
6
3. “State agency” means any board, commission, department,
6
7
authority, bureau, office, or other entity created with authority to
7
8
make rules or formulate orders as defined in the Administrative
8
9
Procedures Act.
9
10
SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
10
11
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 9302 of Title 74, unless there
11
12
is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
12
13
A. Except as provided in subsection B of this section, no state
13
14
agency shall use the term “West Bank” to refer to Judea and Samaria
14
15
in an official government material or use state funds to create an
15
16
official government material that refers to Judea and Samaria as
16
17
West Bank.
17
18
B. The executive head of a state agency may waive the
18
19
prohibition provided for in subsection A of this section if the
19
20
executive head:
20
21
1. Determines that it is in the best interest of the state to
21
22
do so; and
22
23
2. Electronically submits to the Governor, the President Pro
23
24
Tempore of the Senate, and the Speaker of the House of
24
Req. No. 2518 Page 2

1
Representatives a written explanation of such determination no later
1
2
than thirty (30) days after the date on which the executive head of
2
3
the state agency makes such determination.
3
4
SECTION 4. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
